***Describes Fracas Has Claims For Supremacy IBADAN – It has been confirmed that some hoodlums that are responsible for break down of peace and order at Agugu/Oremeji axis of Ibadan on Friday have been arrested by the Police. There is a new developments to the earlier reported clash between Park Managers System (PMS) officials and the so called ‘Federal Boys’ on Thursday and Friday at Agugu/Oremeji area of Ibadan as Oyo State Police Public Relations Officer SP. Adewale Osifeso in a press statement put the record straight. Oyo Police Arrest Suspects Involved In PMS, ‘Federal… Ondo Boosts Security With CIG Pickups, Trucks, Others A press statement made available to INDEPENDENT on Sunday cleared the aired that the incident was a cult related violence. Osifeso through the statement however confirmed that a person was killed during the heated fracas, while some hoodlums that responsible for the break down of law and order have been arrested for thourogh investigations. The statement stated as thus; “Cult related violence broke out at the early hours of Friday 11/02/2022 between some hoodlums around Oremeji Area, Ibadan. “Upon the strength of a distress call received by operatives of the Oyo State Police Command deployments of operational and tactical assets were swiftly executed.” “Preliminary investigation reveals that the violence was as result of claims for supremacy among the hoodlums and in the process a gang member lost his life with others injured while motorcycles and vehicles were vandalized.” POLL “Meanwhile, Normalcy has returned to the area as it remains under close monitoring and surveillance with high visibility policing and intensive patrols.” “Arrests have been made and efforts are ongoing to break the criminal network for the apprehension of other criminal elements within and outside the jurisdiction.” Osifeso stated. Concluded part of the statement maintained that, “Further developments would be communicated accordingly, please.”